    "As the adjacency matrices of graphs are typically sparse, instead of taking all the negative entries when training one typically performs subsampling of entries with A ij = 0.",
    "We extend this neural architecture by adding a feedforward component operating on the latent space and account for its effectiveness via the mean squared error loss term that is added to the optimisation objective.",
    "More specifically, we optimise the following loss function:",
    "where ν(Z) is the predictive model operating on the latent space embedding Z associated with graph (X, A), y is the vector with target labels, and N is the number of labelled instances.",
    "Figure 2 illustrates the setting and our approach to transfer learning using supervised variational graph autoencoders."
